    <text id="A0018T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Captain John Avis writes to Colonel Kenton Harper requesting Harper's advice on
                    troop placement and his aide in procuring Minnie Rifles.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-06-18">June 18th 1861</date>
                        <name type="place">Head Quarters Company K<lb/>Winchester </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Colonel">Col</abbr> Harper<lb/>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have not succeeded in getting the Minnie Rifles yet. I have another plan on
                    foot now It is to have the Enclosed Requisition Signed <hi rend="underline">by
                        Yourself</hi> and <abbr expan="Colonel">Col</abbr> Jackson. Will you be kind
                    Enough to do the best you can for me as I am very anxious to be prepared to do
                    Service Learn from <abbr expan="Colonel">Col</abbr> Jackson if you please if it
                    is necessary to keep those men of my company who are guarding the Winchester and
                    Potomac Rail Road and <unclear>Opequon</unclear> Bridges any Longer on that
                    Service.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>John Avis<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> 5th Infantry</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
